  "local_port": 40104,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is the use of a meta tag in HTML?",
  "response": "Meta tags in HTML serve various functions that are integral to the operation and optimization of web pages. Here are some of their primary uses:\n\n1. **SEO (Search Engine Optimization)**: Meta tags help search engines understand the content and context of a web page. Common meta tags used for SEO include:\n   - **Meta description**: Provides a summary of the page content, which search engines may display in search results.\n   - **Meta keywords**: Although less significant for modern search engines, it lists keywords relevant to the page's content.\n   - **Meta robots**: Guides search engine crawlers on how to index the page (e.g., whether to index the page, follow links, etc.).\n\n2. **Character Encoding**: Specifies the character set used on the web page, ensuring that text is displayed correctly. The tag might look like this:\n   ```html\n   <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n   ```\n\n3. **Viewport Settings**: Controls the layout and scaling on mobile devices, improving responsiveness. It typically includes settings like these:\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n   ```\n\n4. **Author and Content Attribution**: Provides information about the author of the web page or content details. For example:\n   ```html\n   <meta name=\"author\" content=\"John Doe\">\n   ```\n\n5. **HTTP Headers Information**: Defines various headers that can be used by browsers or web crawlers. For instance, specifying the cache-control or setting specific security policies:\n   ```html\n   <meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"30\">\n   ```\n\n6. **Social Media Integration**: Enhances the display of content when shared on social media platforms. Open Graph tags for Facebook and Twitter Cards are examples:\n   ```html\n   <meta property=\"og:title\" content=\"The Title\"/>\n   <meta property=\"og:description\" content=\"The description\"/>\n   ```\n\n7. **Page Redirection**: Automatically redirects visitors to another page after a certain time interval:\n   ```html\n   <meta http-equiv=\"refresh\" content=\"5;url=http://example.com\">\n   ```\n\nBy incorporating meta tags into your HTML, you can improve the discoverability, compatibility, and usability of your web pages, making them more accessible to both users and search engines.",
